# ASR — Automatic Speech Recognition

> Technical-English name kept by exception: ASR is a term of art
> (cf. CUTLASS, NCCL), not a generic utility cloak. The English name
> is the honest name here.

## Philosophical Role

The ASR module is the specific kernel of Auditus that converts mel
features into token IDs. It is a sub-subsystem of Auditus because its
lifecycle (model-load, encoder, decoder, mel extraction) is tight
enough that cross-wiring it with VAD/FRCRN/MossFormer2 would pollute
both sides.

A Whisper-family encoder-decoder, streamable, GPTQ-quantizable,
operating on 80-bin mel features at 100 Hz frame rate.

## Contract with Surrounding Subsystems

- **Auditus** owns the lifecycle; ASR is never instantiated outside
  Auditus.
- **Machina** provides the GEMM primitives (cuBLAS / cuTLASS); ASR
  provides the operator sequences specific to the Whisper topology.
- **Conscientia** never sees ASR directly — it sees tokens arriving
  through `auditus_facade`.

## Current State

`asr_encoder.cu`, `asr_decoder.cu`, `asr_ops.cu`, `whisper_mel.cu`,
plus their public headers. All within R1 as of 2026-04-23.
